{"months":[],"name":"Three Tzemoleras (Chiflon)","rappelCountMin":3,"latitude":16.1946,"longitude":-92.2658,"vehicle":null,"rappelLongestMeters":70,"id":11365,"technicalRating":4,"description":"<div class=\"mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><p>Near the town of Tzimol, the San Vicente River turbulent waters create a majestic set of waterfalls as they descend down the mountain. These waterfalls are named 'El Suspiro', 'Ala de Ángel', 'Arcoíris', 'Quinceañera' y 'Velo de Novia' (the tallest at 70m), and are collectively known as 'Cascadas El Chiflón' and abbreviated as 'Chiflón'. Two commercial Ecotouristic centers, one located at each side of the river, cater to tourists providing hiking trails to access viewing platforms and swimming holes created by the falls.\n<\/p><p>This area is also home of a kick-ass canyoneering route called 'Three Tzemoleras'. Local adventure companies (Xaman, Petra and Explora) joined forces and run the first descent of this canyon in 2015 and will be offering this trip publicly in 2016. \n<\/p><p>Experienced canyoneers may also choose to descend this canyoneering route on their own, as long as they use proper techniques and don't get into trouble.\n<\/p>\n<meta property=\"mw:PageProp\/toc\" \/>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Approach\">Approach<\/h2><\/div>\n<p>The route requires a shuttle. Leave a vehicle at the exit of Chiflon and with another vehicles transfer up the mountain to the town of Tzemoleras. \n<\/p><p>The road to Tzemoleras is said to require a 4 wheel drive vehicle. If you don't have any, arrange transport with some of the locals. Given the distance from Tuxla, it may be preferable to arrange to stay for the night at Tzemoleras to start the canyon fresh the next morning.\n<\/p><p>The location of the approach and drop in point in the map are approximations, please contact James Wright (Xaman) for more information.\n<\/p>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Descent\">Descent<\/h2><\/div>\n<p>The descent includes 3 main waterfalls of 30m, 60m &amp; 70m high plus several smaller ones all the way to Chiflon (the area of the river controlled by the cooperativas)\n<\/p>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Exit\">Exit<\/h2><\/div>\n<p>Hike down the tourists trails to the parking lot and your vehicle.\n<\/p>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Red_tape\">Red tape<\/h2><\/div>\n<ul><li>as of late September 2021, we were told (by the ejido on the UCR side of the river) that it is not permitted to run this canyon. It was unclear whether this was due to the high flow at the time or whether this would apply year-round. Follow ups in the dry season would help to clarify the situation. We could find no information about the guide companies Xaman or Petra in either Comitan or near the tourist site.<\/li><\/ul>\n<p>The 'cooperativas' that run 'Chiflon' refuse permission to rappel the falls to commercial companies, claiming they want to run their own canyoneering trips in future. It is not clear if they would be more permissive with private groups.\n<\/p>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Beta_sites\">Beta sites<\/h2><\/div>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http:\/\/www.mexicodesconocido.com.mx\/guia-de-cascadas-de-chiapas.html\">http:\/\/www.mexicodesconocido.com.mx\/guia-de-cascadas-de-chiapas.html<\/a><\/li><\/ul>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Trip_reports_and_media\">Trip reports and media<\/h2><\/div>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"https:\/\/www.facebook.com\/media\/set\/?set=a.1706052862947235.1073741859.1482144422004748&amp;type=3\">https:\/\/www.facebook.com\/media\/set\/?set=a.1706052862947235.1073741859.1482144422004748&amp;type=3<\/a> Facebook Album first descent<\/li><\/ul>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Background\">Background<\/h2><\/div>\n<p>Original information provided by James Wright (Xaman) and Carlos Macotela (Petra).\n<\/p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw‐api‐ext.codfw.main‐6779cc57fc‐74czk\nCached time: 20240914192014\nCache expiry: 2592000\nReduced expiry: false\nComplications: [show‐toc]\nCPU time usage: 0.008 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.009 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 21\/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 0\/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0\/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2\/100\nExpensive parser function count: 0\/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0\/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 0\/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0\/400\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    0.000      1 -total\n-->\n<\/div>","url":"https:\/\/ropewiki.com\/Three_Tzemoleras_(Chiflon)","riskRating":"R","shuttleSeconds":null,"geojson":{"type":"FeatureCollection","features":[{"properties":{"name":"Approach?"},"type":"Feature","geometry":{"coordinates":[[-92.24864589843492,16.219603948351274,0],[-92.24865662727098,16.219583344732666,0],[-92.24893557700852,16.218996140696106,0],[-92.24909650954942,16.218666481522355,0],[-92.24905359420518,16.21706968709123,0],[-92.24821674499253,16.21662670311684,0],[-92.24783050689439,16.21598798028393,0],[-92.24780904922227,16.21596737628709,0],[-92.24775540504197,16.215915866285595,0],[-92.24753009948472,16.215709826144895,0],[-92.24696153240075,16.21572276219595,0],[-92.24695616798272,16.21572276219595,0],[-92.24659138755669,16.216011218313643,0],[-92.24603885249962,16.216165748202954,0],[-92.24603885249962,16.216170899197174,0],[-92.24554532604088,16.215964859323208,0],[-92.24525564746727,16.215387946529727,0],[-92.24525564746727,16.215387946529727,0],[-92.2449552400576,16.21480588101711,0],[-92.2449552400576,16.214780125866206,0],[-92.24471384124627,16.21402807397532,0],[-92.24471384124627,16.21402807397532,0],[-92.24424177245965,16.21429077735932,0],[-92.24424177245965,16.21429077735932,0],[-92.24407547550072,16.21287938643708,0]],"type":"LineString"}},{"type":"Fe